The President is closely monitoring recovery efforts after Hurricane Ida and has directed the Federal government to take prompt actions to help those affected. He has spoken with the Governors of Louisiana and Mississippi, as well as mayors and parish leaders in the affected areas. The Federal government will coordinate with local and private sector partners to provide support. The President authorized actions to assist with power restoration efforts and has spoken with electricity sector leaders to ensure ongoing support. The FEMA Administrator has visited Louisiana and Mississippi to assess damage and discuss recovery efforts. Emergency Declarations were approved for Louisiana and Mississippi before the hurricane hit, allowing FEMA to provide assistance for emergency measures. Resources were pre-positioned in the region, including search and rescue equipment, meals, water, generators, and personnel. The Administration has taken swift action, including approving a Major Disaster Declaration for Louisiana, providing assistance to disaster survivors, expediting power restoration, increasing the availability of gasoline, and restoring critical communications.